The president of Dangote Group, Aliko Dangote yesterday won “the Philanthropic Person of the Year 2018 Award” by the Leadership Newspapers. The Newspaper said it recognised Dangote as Africa’s greatest giver, affirming that “his heart and his generosity are as expanse as the size of a vault”. In his response, the Africa’s richest man, Aliko said that giving back to the Society gives him a sense of purpose in life. Represented by GED of the Group, Engr. Mansur Ahmed, Dangote said giving back to the society helps him contribute to the common good. Chairman, Leadership Group, Sam-Nda Isaiah, said in recognition of Dangote’s giant strides and unprecedented good works for the year 2018, the company had tagged him “Philanthropic Aliko” . The Etsu Nupe, Alhaji Yahaya Abubakar; the Ooni of Ife, Oba Adeyeye Enitan Ogunwusi; tOba Aladetoyinbo Ogunlade Aladelusi of Akure Kingdom; Alhaji Ahmed Joda and Justice Sylvanus Nsofor, in their good will messages, preached against violence, corruption.  Dangote bags ABU corporate award UN chief hails Dangote’s interventions Dangote feeds 30,000 IDPs in Zamfara